item.dc:creator: @HeWhoOpensADoor HeWhoOpensADoor
item.description:
@HeWhoOpensADoor wrote:

I have a completely customized PC that I built my self…heres some of the specs of it ^.^

-Dual NVidia 8800 GTX GPUS
-Intel Quad-Core Xenon Processor 2.66 Ghz (it USED to be 2.66 ghz until I overclocked it to 3.5 Ghz :))
-24 Inch LCD High-Def Monitor that I built my self ^.^
-Kick Ass NVidia Motherboard (Not the real name…I just forgot the name of it :p)
-Water Based Cooling System (Forgot the name…but it keeps my computers CPU and other componets at a nice and cool 35 Degrees to prevent overheating which leads to a computer meltdown (literally…ever seen a CPU MELT before? I have…and it aint pretty))
-Windows Vista Ultimate…Yes I know…it sucks so please don’t be all “LOLZ J00 H4v3 WINDOZ VIZTA J00 R LIEK SO GAI LULZ!!1!!!” I seriously don’t think a Mac OS could possibly handle my computers power :s (sorry to all ye Bill gates haters…) but hey…at least I didn’t actually PAY for Vista and give that greedy ass Bill Gates 400 bucks of my cold hard cash…I know the right sites hehehehe and also…even though I downloaded it…it works perfectly ^.^

yeah…basically my computer kicks the ass of those “Commercial” brand computers…except MAYBE Alienware…
